<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>em2johns</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jul 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Been reading some posts, and have been trying to figure in how specialization and SCM3 equates to manna preservation.  I read a couple passing comments that lead me to believe that specializing up to 200 in something gives you something like 10% manna preservation, kinda like an obulus death shroud.  Having SCM3 adds 10% manna preservation on your specialization (for 20% total), and gives you the full 20% manna preservation on non specialized skills?<br />
Is this right?  Anyone know, or know where I can look?<br />
---<br />
edit: I just wanted to quote Nytmare as it seems to be the general concensus of this post.  Hopefully this will save future folks using the search feature some reading.  <br />
<br />
I just got SCM3. It has two benefits.<br />
<br />
After test casting Khura's several times, I see it uses the same amount of mana every time. My Magelo profile tells me how much mana I have.<br />
<br />
Without SCM,<br />
Alteration spells save about 10-12% mana due to specialization in alteration.<br />
Non-alt spells save 0.<br />
<br />
With SCM3,<br />
Alteration spells save about 20-24%.<br />
Non-alt spells save about 10-12%.<br />
<br />
So SCM3 seems to save a flat 10-12% mana on all spells - on top of your chosen specialization (Alteration).<br />
<br />
In addition, spells that used to fizzle a lot even at max casting skill - Torrent of Poison - now have minimum fizzles with SCM3. The fizzlefest is gone!</p>
	
	
	
	
