	<p>Turley: Heh, you caught me, I'm a literature major by nature, and I only do math when its related to the CS stuff I randomly study.  If your numbers are right (and I'll assume they are, though I always like to see formulas so I can educate myself on what I did wrong, if you don't mind explaining them that is) then again Hann's results are off by a bit, 3.7% instead of 3%, and in the other direction.  This would seem to indicate SCM works even better when you cast MGB.  But then again since Hann didn't keep tabs on his gear, it could just be that.  Until someone does something similiar, with the exact same gear before and after, we won't know for sure.<br />
<br />
Jharassik:  You're right, all the qualifying statements ("by this logic," etc.) came before that one line "So to answer your original question:".  I guess I can see how you could think I was trying to present this as fact, if you just kind of ignored the paragraph before it.  I still prolly should have written "So to answer your original question, I think:" or something like that.  But I'd like to assume some basic intelligence on the part of my reader, and therefore hope that they could remember my qualifying statments from earlier in the post, thus saving me the time of having to keep repeating them.</p>
	
	
	
