	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />I was saving AAs for SCM. I had 11 AA saved one day and was close to my 12th. I stopped the pulls and cast MGB Khuras (don't have Fo7) when I was at 100% mana. That used 51% of my mana leaving me at 49%. Not too long later I got my 12th point and went from no points spent into SCM to SCM3. When MGB popped later I cast MGB Khuras again. That used 44% of my mana leaving me at 56%.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Operating under the assumption that you are Alter spec'd...<br />
<br />
MGB Khura's, 200 spec, no SCM, no Mana Preservation = 2500 * .9 = 2250. Using 51% of your mana means your mana pool is around 2250/.51 = 4411 (4500 to 4326 depending on UI rounding).<br />
<br />
With SCM3, 44% used is somewhere between 1980 and 1903. Those would represent savings of 21.8% (1- 1980/2500) and 23.88% (1- 1903/2500). <br />
<br />
Consistent with the commonly accepted values.</p>
	
	
	
