<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Turley</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Dec 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Zyphyr</b><br /><i>Operating under the assumption that you are Alter spec'd...<br />
<br />
MGB Khura's, 200 spec, no SCM, no Mana Preservation = 2500 * .9 = 2250. Using 51% of your mana means your mana pool is around 2250/.51 = 4411 (4500 to 4326 depending on UI rounding).<br />
<br />
With SCM3, 44% used is somewhere between 1980 and 1903. Those would represent savings of 21.8% (1- 1980/2500) and 23.88% (1- 1903/2500). <br />
<br />
Consistent with the commonly accepted values.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I was not counting the savings from specialization into the %.<br />
<br />
The difference between having SCM3 and not is 13.7%<br />
<br />
The total saving from specialization + SCM3 is (51/.9)-44)/(51/.9) * 100% = 22.3%  which is what you calculated.<br />
<br />
Just wanted to make clear to the other posters, both calculations are correct just represent different things.  <img src="images/smilies/cool.gif" border="0" alt="" title="cool" smilieid="7" /></p>
	
	
	
	
	
