</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I just got SCM3. It has two benefits.<br />
<br />
After test casting Khura's several times, I see it uses the same amount of mana every time. My Magelo profile tells me how much mana I have.<br />
<br />
Without SCM,<br />
Alteration spells save about 10-12% mana due to specialization in alteration.<br />
Non-alt spells save 0.<br />
<br />
With SCM3,<br />
Alteration spells save about 20-24%.<br />
Non-alt spells save about 10-12%.<br />
<br />
So SCM3 seems to save a flat 10-12% mana on all spells - on top of your chosen specialization (Alteration).<br />
<br />
In addition, spells that used to fizzle a lot even at max casting skill - Torrent of Poison - now have minimum fizzles with SCM3. The fizzlefest is gone!</p>
	
	
	
