	<!-- message -->
	<p>My shaman has been basically parked in the Bazaar for about a year. A month ago, I pulled him out and got him his last 5 levels, and another 55 aa.<br />
<br />
The first thing I did AA-wise was get him MC3 and then Cana 5. Awesome ability. I got killed the other day by repops while we already had 2 mobs in camp. I got a quick rez, looted while cleric and pally rebuffed me, summoned my lizzy mount, cast Quie on myself, cana 5, turned around and slowed the 2 mobs that had killed me. Try that without cana 5. Even the group was laughing about the "no down time shaman". <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
<br />
The next aa ability was SCM3. I had known from my playing over a year ago that SCM was uber. When SoL first came out, I had gotten SCM1 and could see the difference in my mana with that, and later got SCM2 as well. SCM3 is the difference between me having enough mana for that one last heal to win the tough fight, or loosing due to being OOM.<br />
<br />
Cana 5 and SCM3 together are almost godly. I dont sit here and nit pick through the numbers, but I can see when something is working. And SCM3 works. And is obvious. SCRM is also a *HUGE* difference.<br />
<br />
We get some nice AA's... maybe too many... :lol</p>
	
	
	
